-- 
Big Clothing Companies Set Ecological Label Standards, FT Says

-- B y   B l a n c h e   G a t t
-- 
2011-03-01T01:45:35Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-01/big-clothing-companies-set-ecological-label-standards-ft-says.html
Clothing and footwear makers and
retailers are planning to label their products with information
about the impact on the environment of the manufacture and use
of the item, the Financial Times reported, citing  Wal-Mart
Stores Inc .’s Vice-President of Product Development for
Clothing, Alex Tomey.  The companies, which include Wal-Mart,  Gap Inc ., JC Penney
Co., Levi Strauss & Co., Nike Inc., Marks & Spencer Group Plc,
Adidas AG, Hennes & Mauritz AB and Li & Fung Ltd., decided on a
“collaborative approach” to pool “all the answers” and find
“the correct way of measuring all the variables involved,” the
newspaper said, citing Tomey.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blanche Gatt in London at 
 bgatt@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Colin Keatinge at 
 ckeatinge@bloomberg.net . 